      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/10917.Stephen_Fry">About Stephen Fry</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/10917.Stephen_Fry"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1400162446p3/10917.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/10917.Stephen_Fry">Stephen Fry
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
8,135
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer9340120549234582560">Stephen John Fry is an English comedian, writer, actor, humourist, novelist, poet, columnist, filmmaker, television personality and technophile. As one half of the Fry and Laurie double act with his comedy partner, Hugh Laurie, he has appeared in <i>A Bit of Fry and Laurie</i> and <i>Jeeves and Wooster</i>. He is also famous for his roles in <i>Blackadder</i> and <i>Wilde</i>, and as the host of QI. In addition to writing fo</span>
  <span id="freeText9340120549234582560" style="display:none">Stephen John Fry is an English comedian, writer, actor, humourist, novelist, poet, columnist, filmmaker, television personality and technophile. As one half of the Fry and Laurie double act with his comedy partner, Hugh Laurie, he has appeared in <i>A Bit of Fry and Laurie</i> and <i>Jeeves and Wooster</i>. He is also famous for his roles in <i>Blackadder</i> and <i>Wilde</i>, and as the host of QI. In addition to writing for stage, screen, television and radio he has contributed columns and articles for numerous newspapers and magazines, and has also written four successful novels and a series of memoirs.<br /><br />See also <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/5797221.Mrs_Stephen_Fry" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <i>Mrs. Stephen Fry</i>
</a> as a pseudonym of the author.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9340120549234582560" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>

  

